      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "As a consequence of new snow and a moderate to strong northeasterly wind, sometimes avalanche prone wind slabs will form in the late morning in particular in places that are protected from the wind. In all aspects medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large slab avalanches are possible. In particular in the regions with a lot of snow the avalanches can penetrate even deep layers.",
        "highlights": "The new snow and wind slabs represent the main danger. Above approximately 1800 m the wind slabs are larger. Wind slabs are to be evaluated with care and prudence."
